<div id="review_4095648096" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4095648096" />
    <a title="Ivonne Rovira" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3803671-ivonne-rovira"><img alt="Ivonne Rovira" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1339470651p2/3803671.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4095648096?book_show_action=true">Jul 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ivonne Rovira" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ivonne Rovira" href="/user/show/3803671-ivonne-rovira">Ivonne Rovira</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780590929974" href="/book/show/1137392.A_Bad_Case_of_Stripes">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3803671-ivonne-rovira?shelf=children-literature">children-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4095648096" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15034621484231976687">The theme of this classic — be yourself — might be trite, but the book’s treatment of the topic is anything but. Camila Cream, obsessive about what others think, becomes sick with stripes! Young readers will love seeing the doctors try to cure Camila and to see what finally makes her illness go away; adults probably won’t like the book as much as kids do, but it’s still a fun read. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


