<span id="freeTextContainer2513417354892041513">Breaking my strict rule about avoiding David Shannon books, I checked this one out after I noticed that almost every goodreads friend I have is reading it or wants to read it. The illustrations are AMAZING. Perhaps the best I&apos;ve ever seen in a picture book. The story is . . . meh. It&apos;s a little too old for Catherine, and kind of saccharine. A pretty standard version of the just-be-yourself bit.</span>
  <span id="freeText2513417354892041513" style="display:none">Breaking my strict rule about avoiding David Shannon books, I checked this one out after I noticed that almost every goodreads friend I have is reading it or wants to read it. The illustrations are AMAZING. Perhaps the best I've ever seen in a picture book. The story is . . . meh. It's a little too old for Catherine, and kind of saccharine. A pretty standard version of the just-be-yourself bit.</span>
